    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nbfdddec8bab85340b4b293f1467a56f495e26c2f\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nn/a\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nn/a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nn/a\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nThe return type of `nvim_buf_get_extmark_by_id` is allegedly a `ArrayOf(Integer)`, but this is not true when `opts = {\"details\": true}`, in which case `nvim_buf_get_extmark_by_id` also returns the details dictionary.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/bfdddec8bab85340b4b293f1467a56f495e26c2f/src/nvim/api/extmark.c#L208\r\n\r\nI think this should be `Array` instead.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n```\r\nnvim --api-info | python -c 'import msgpack, sys, yaml; yaml.dump(msgpack.unpackb(sys.stdin.buffer.read()), sys.stdout)' | grep extmark_by_id -A10\r\n  name: nvim_buf_get_extmark_by_id\r\n  parameters:\r\n  - - Buffer\r\n    - buffer\r\n  - - Integer\r\n    - ns_id\r\n  - - Integer\r\n    - id\r\n  - - Dictionary\r\n    - opts\r\n  return_type: Array\r\n```\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n```\r\nnvim --api-info | python -c 'import msgpack, sys, yaml; yaml.dump(msgpack.unpackb(sys.stdin.buffer.read()), sys.stdout)' | grep extmark_by_id -A10\r\n  name: nvim_buf_get_extmark_by_id\r\n  parameters:\r\n  - - Buffer\r\n    - buffer\r\n  - - Integer\r\n    - ns_id\r\n  - - Integer\r\n    - id\r\n  - - Dictionary\r\n    - opts\r\n  return_type: ArrayOf(Integer)\r\n```",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-16T04:12:11Z",
